<exercise checkit-seed="0006" checkit-slug="FO4" checkit-title="Exact First-Order IVPs">
  <statement>
    <p>
        Explain why one of the following ODEs is exact, and why the other is not.
    </p>
      <me>5 \, t^{2} {y'} - 2 \, t {y'} = 10 \, t y^{2} + 3 \, y^{2}</me><me>10 \, t y^{2} = -10 \, t^{2} y {y'} - 6 \, t y {y'} + 12 \, t^{2} - 3 \, y^{2}</me>
    <p>
      Then find an implicit solution for the exact ODE
      that satisfies the initial value
        <m>y(-1)=1</m>.
    </p>
  </statement>
  <answer>
    <p>The following ODE is exact.</p>
      <me>10 \, t y^{2} = -10 \, t^{2} y {y'} - 6 \, t y {y'} + 12 \, t^{2} - 3 \, y^{2}</me>
    <p>
      Its implicit solution satisfying the initial value is:
    </p>
      <me>-5 \, t^{2} y^{2} + 4 \, t^{3} - 3 \, t y^{2} = \left(-6\right)</me>
  </answer>
</exercise>
